| Finding | Confidence | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| **Defect 1** — Equip without bag check | **95%** | Directly observed: equip item 99 succeeded before additem 99 in same batch. Repeated with item 3 after removal. |
| **Defect 2** — Duplicate slot equip | **98%** | Reproduced twice: item 1 in weapon+armor, item 99 after item 3 in weapon slot. Clear pattern. |
| **Defect 3** — Duplicate reward claim | **90%** | Observed "reward claimed again" log for days 1, 2, 3, 5, 7. Logs say "again" but never say "failed". Ambiguous whether items are actually re-granted or just logged. |
| **Defect 4** — Equip after remove | **92%** | Clearly observed in batch 7: remove then equip of item 3 succeeded. |
| **Defect 5** — Silent unequip failure | **85%** | No log line at all for helmet unequip. Could be filtered at a layer not visible in logs, but likely a silent failure. |
| **Defect 6** — Achievement mail no attachment | **80%** | Mail 2 explicitly said "has no attachment". Could be by design, but worth flagging. |
| **Defect 7** — collector_100 not triggering | **70%** | Achievement was created but never unlocked. Total items well exceeded 100. May require a different condition, but appears buggy. |
| **Defect 8** — Tasks never complete | **65%** | Tasks were created with targets, but no progress was ever logged. The trigger mechanism may simply not have been exercised correctly. |

**Overall Assessment:** The most critical issues are in the **Equipment module**, which lacks bag ownership validation and item-uniqueness enforcement. The **SignIn/Reward module** also allows duplicate claims. These are the highest-priority fixes. Batch execution processes operations sequentially but each operation validates state independently without considering prior operations in the same batch, leading to consistency violations.
